From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: slothfulchat <dev@slothfulchat.local>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 01:11:05 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 47/64] web-app: enlarge chat navbar button click targets

The chat title-bar icon buttons (apps, map, three-dot menu) had a 20x20px
click target sitting in a 50px-tall navbar with a 12px dead gap between
them, so most of the bar was unclickable. Grow each button's hit box to
fill the vertical dead space and the inter-button gap, and cancel the
growth with negative margins so the icons and navbar height stay
pixel-for-pixel identical.
---
 .../components/ChatView/styles.module.scss    | 19 +++++++++++++++----
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/packages/frontend/src/components/ChatView/styles.module.scss b/packages/frontend/src/components/ChatView/styles.module.scss
index c81615c..28e5e10 100644
--- a/packages/frontend/src/components/ChatView/styles.module.scss
+++ b/packages/frontend/src/components/ChatView/styles.module.scss
@@ -62,17 +62,28 @@
 
     :global(.navbar-button) {
       padding: 0;
-      width: 20px;
-      height: 20px;
+      // Enlarge the click target without changing anything visible: the icon
+      // stays centered in a bigger box and negative margins cancel out the
+      // added size, so icon positions and the navbar height are pixel-for-pixel
+      // identical to before. Previously the box was only 20x20 inside a 50px
+      // navbar, with a 12px (dead, unclickable) gap between buttons.
+      $hit-width: 32px; // reclaims the 12px inter-button gap (6px each side)
+      $hit-height: 40px; // reclaims the 50px navbar's vertical dead space
+      width: $hit-width;
+      height: $hit-height;
+      // Keep the icon exactly where it was and the row footprint unchanged:
+      // shift the wider box back by half the growth, and shrink the trailing
+      // gap by the same amount (12px stays the icon-to-icon spacing).
+      margin-inline-start: calc((20px - #{$hit-width}) / 2);
+      margin-inline-end: calc(12px + (20px - #{$hit-width}) / 2);
       border-radius: 0;
-      margin-inline-end: 12px;
       &:hover {
         background-color: var(--navBarButtonHover);
       }
     }
 
     :global(#three-dot-menu-button) {
-      height: 20px;
+      height: 40px;
     }
   }
 }
